social_posts.post_text: Long walks in the woods like this make me feel at peace.
Some of the buffalo of Yellowstone plus a bonus capture at the end.
Taggart Lake. Last photo of 2022 for me. I hope everyone has success and happiness in the coming year. Cheers.
Lily pad lake, can you spot the toad?
The stunning Nāpali Coast as seen from above. I got the unique opportunity to fly in a door-less helicopter and take some photos of this beautiful landscape.
4 days in Kauai
Beautiful details of Hawaii
More of the Kauai landscape

Dreaming of those warm Hawaiian waters. 

#beach #beachvibes #beachlife #beachday #beachview #ocean #oceanlife #hawaii #hawaiian #hawaiilife #hawaiistagram #hawaiian #hawaiianislands #kauai #kauaihawaii
Waterfalls on Kauai
Queensbath, Kauai. We saw sea turtles and powerful waves crashing down. Crazy to think people swim here at times
I enjoy waterfalls, even the small ones.
Hanging lake, CO. A bit of a butt kicker to get to (incline not length) but we’ll worth the views.
Day one of @glaciernps did not disappoint. I know a lot come for the peaks but the rivers had my attention today.
Hidden lake overlook at Glacier National Park. The weather on the hike up was pretty bad but just as we approached the overlook, the skies parted and gave a beautiful view.
Views from Grinnell Glacier. This hike was challenging but absolutely rewarding. In my opinion, it’s the one hike you must do while in @glaciernps
Morning hike to Avalanche Lake in @glaciernps was wonderful. The forest and river leading up to the lake was just as amazing as the lake itself.
Some more views of Glacier. McDonald Lake, Grinnell Glacier and the stunning river system.
Some of the wildlife shots I captured from glacier earlier this fall. Great seeing all these animals out in their natural habitat.
Fall in @glaciernps and views along the “going to the sun” road.
Days like these are the best.
Peace and solitude; great way to start any adventure.
Exploring new trails and amazing views never gets old.
No caption needed, simply serene
